{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2315c3a1-2493-4b0b-b11d-966256d34845","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Target Framework Problems:**\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** (for .NET Core) and **.NET Framework 4.6.2+**. Your project targets:\n\n| Framework | MSTest v3 Compatible? |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ No — EOL, not supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ No — EOL, not supported |\n\nYou'll need to update your .NET Core targets to at least `net6.0` (preferably `net8.0`).\n\n**Package Changes:**\nMSTest v3 consolidates into a single `MSTest` package, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd update the csproj roughly like:\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n...\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1cafa8d6-f3a7-4cb1-be10-65bce4bbc39c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. Let me check what MSTest v3 supports in terms of target frameworks.\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest 3.x) dropped support for several older frameworks:\n- .NET 5.0 is EOL and not supported by MSTest v3\n- .NET Core 3.1 is EOL and not supported by MSTest v3\n- .NET Framework 4.6.2 — MSTest v3 still supports .NET Framework, but the minimum is typically 4.6.2, so this should be okay.\n\n\n- Actually, MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0 or later for the .NET side, so `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` won't work, but `net462` is fine. The framework also switched to using the unified `MSTest` meta-package instead of separate adapter and framework packages, though that's not directly relevant to the compatibility question.","outputTokens":571,"requestId":"0838:1E21:70442DF:7D65BD9:69EAD57E"},"id":"116c6ee6-f5cb-4d69-a484-c06fa539cef3","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:29:29.779Z","parentId":"83161054-5817-4